This paper deals with computational aspects of voting rules, which is a topic in computational social choice (cs.GT). The paper also discusses the difficulty of manipulating voting rules, which is a problem that can be approached using artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The authors use empirical studies to improve their understanding of the issue, which involves data analysis and statistical methods (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the probability of manipulating voting rules, which is a topic in machine learning and probabilistic modeling (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses the impact of correlated and uncorrelated voters on the difficulty of manipulation, which is a topic in social influence and network analysis (cs.SI).
